==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc}} {{term|μελαγχολία||[[atrabiliousness]]|tr=melancholia|lang=grc}}, from {{term|μέλας||tr=melas|lang=grc}}, {{term|μελαν-||black, dark, murky|tr=melan-|lang=grc}} + {{term|χολή||bile|tr=chole|lang=grc}}. Compare the Latin {{term|atra bilis|ātra bīlis|black bile|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈmɛl.ənˌkɑl.i/}}
* {{audio|En-us-melancholy.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Affected with great [[sadness]] or [[depression]].

